  "body": "RPC Server returns error when an non-existing transaction is requested. Should return just `null`\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nDebian\r\nerigon version 2021.12.3-beta\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ curl --request POST  --url http://127.0.0.1:8545/ --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\r\n  --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\", \"method\":\"eth_getTransactionByHash\", \"id\":1, \"params\":[\"0x00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff\"]}'\r\n\r\n{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\"id\": 1,\"result\": null}\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ curl --request POST  --url http://127.0.0.1:8545/ --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\r\n  --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\", \"method\":\"eth_getTransactionByHash\", \"id\":1, \"params\":[\"0x00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff\"]}'\r\n\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"error\":{\"code\":-32000,\"message\":\"rpc error: code = Unavailable desc = connection closed before server preface received\"}}\r\n```\r\n",
